General Data Protection Regulation

   The data you will provide by applying is automatically processed by
   the HR department, as a controller, to process and manage your
   application. This data processing is necessary to run your
   application. The data protection officer can be contacted at the
   following e-mail address dpo@weekendesk.fr

   The data will be kept two years after the last contact with the
   candidate if the position is not assigned to him. In case of hiring,
   the data can be kept by the employer for the duration of the employment
   contract. The recipients of the data are the HR department.

   As part of its processing operations, the controller will not transfer
   your personal data outside the European Union.

   You have a right of access, rectification and, in case of legitimate
   reason, deletion, limitation and opposition to the processing of your
   data. You also benefit from the right to the portability of your data
   and the possibility to give instructions concerning your data, in case
   of death. You can exercise these rights by sending an email to
   dpo@weekendesk.fr. If you are not satisfied, you have the opportunity
   to contact the CNIL.
